        "timestamp": "2017-09-15 02:00:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(3 comments)\n\nRich thanks for updating commit message and taking care of the merge conflict.\n\nAs an FYI, generally we want to keep code changes in the same changeset and just upload a new patch to the same change set. This helps us with history of the patch both for review sake and in case we need to go back and look at why a patch was merged and what the discussion was about it.\n\nSome style issues were introduced in BaseDBConfiguration.java.\n\nIn light of long wait to get these changes into the code and many attempts I'll ignore the above and +2. But I'll be more stringent in the future.",
